jnxL2tp.name: jnxL2tp
jnxL2tp.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
jnxL2tp.description: Provides monitoring information regarding the Layer Two Transport Protocol. This MIB is based on the standard MIB defined in RFC 3371. However, there are significant differences including the INDEX fields of l2tpTunnelStatsTable and l2tpSessionStatsTable.

jnxL2tpStatsTotalTunnels.name: jnxL2tpStatsTotalTunnels
jnxL2tpStatsTotalTunnels.description: This object returns the total number of tunnels that are currently in the established state. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsTotalSessions.name: jnxL2tpStatsTotalSessions
jnxL2tpStatsTotalSessions.description: This object returns the total number of sessions that are currently in the established state. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsControlRxOctets.name: jnxL2tpStatsControlRxOctets
jnxL2tpStatsControlRxOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets received by the existing tunnels. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsControlRxPkts.name: jnxL2tpStatsControlRxPkts
jnxL2tpStatsControlRxPkts.description: This object returns the number of control packets received by the existing tunnels. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsControlTxOctets.name: jnxL2tpStatsControlTxOctets
jnxL2tpStatsControlTxOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets that were transmitted to the existing tunnel endpoints. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsControlTxPkts.name: jnxL2tpStatsControlTxPkts
jnxL2tpStatsControlTxPkts.description: This object returns the number of control packets that were transmitted to the existing tunnel endpoints.This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsPayloadRxOctets.name: jnxL2tpStatsPayloadRxOctets
jnxL2tpStatsPayloadRxOctets.description: This object returns the number of payload channel octets that were received on the exisiting tunnels. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsPayloadRxPkts.name: jnxL2tpStatsPayloadRxPkts
jnxL2tpStatsPayloadRxPkts.description: This object returns the number of payload packets that were received on the existing tunnels. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsPayloadTxOctets.name: jnxL2tpStatsPayloadTxOctets
jnxL2tpStatsPayloadTxOctets.description: This object returns the number of payload channel octets that were transmitted to the existing tunnel peers. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsPayloadTxPkts.name: jnxL2tpStatsPayloadTxPkts
jnxL2tpStatsPayloadTxPkts.description: This object returns the number of payload packets that were transmitted to existing tunnel peers. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsErrorTxPkts.name: jnxL2tpStatsErrorTxPkts
jnxL2tpStatsErrorTxPkts.description: This object returns the number of errored packet transmission attempts to the existing tunnel peers. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpStatsErrorRxPkts.name: jnxL2tpStatsErrorRxPkts
jnxL2tpStatsErrorRxPkts.description: This object returns the number of errored packets that were received from the existing tunnel peers. This is an instantaneously accumulated value which can increase or decrease depending on number of tunnels established at the time of querying.

jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTable.name: jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTable
jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTable.description: The L2TP tunnel group status and statistics table. This table contains objects that can be used to describe the current status and statistics of a single L2TP tunnel group.

jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsEntry.name: jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsEntry
jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsEntry.description: An L2TP tunnel group stats entry.

jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTnlGrpName.name: jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTnlGrpName
jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTnlGrpName.description: This object contains the name of this tunnel group.

jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsGatewayAddrType.name: jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsGatewayAddrType
jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsGatewayAddrType.description: This object contains the type of local IP address for L2TP tunnels that are part of this group.

jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsGatewayAddr.name: jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsGatewayAddr
jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsGatewayAddr.description: This object contains the local IP address for L2TP tunnels that are part of this group.

jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsSvcIntfName.name: jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsSvcIntfName
jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsSvcIntfName.description: This object contains the name of the service interface that is hosting this tunnel group.

jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTotalTunnels.name: jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTotalTunnels
jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTotalTunnels.description: This object returns the total number of tunnels that are currently in the established state in this tunnel group.

jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTotalSessions.name: jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTotalSessions
jnxL2tpTunnelGroupStatsTotalSessions.description: This object returns the total number of sessions that are currently in the established state in this tunnel group.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsTable.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsTable
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsTable.description: The L2TP tunnel status and statistics table. This table contains objects that can be used to describe the current status and statistics of a single L2TP tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsEntry.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsEntry
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsEntry.description: An L2TP tunnel interface stats entry.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalTID.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalTID
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalTID.description: This object contains the local tunnel Identifier.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsServiceInterface.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsServiceInterface
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsServiceInterface.description: This object contains the name of the service interface on which this tunnel is being hosted.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsTunnelGroup.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsTunnelGroup
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsTunnelGroup.description: This object contains the name of the tunnel group that this tunnel is part of.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteTID.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteTID
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteTID.description: This object contains the remote tunnel Identifier.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteIpAddrType.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteIpAddrType
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteIpAddrType.description: This object contains the type of the remote end address of this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteIpAddress.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteIpAddress
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteIpAddress.description: This object contains the remote end address of this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteUdpPort.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteUdpPort
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteUdpPort.description: This object contains the remote end UDP port of this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsActiveSessions.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsActiveSessions
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsActiveSessions.description: This object contains the total number of sessions in the established state for this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsState.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsState
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsState.description: This field contains the current state of the control tunnel - one of the internal tunnel state names as described below: cc_responder_accept_new The tunnel has received and accepted the start control connection request (SCCRQ) cc_responder_reject_new The tunnel has received and rejected the SCCRQ cc_responder_idle The tunnel has just been created cc_responder_wait_ctl_conn The tunnel has sent the start control connection response (SCCRP) and is waiting for the start control connection connected (SCCCN) message cleanup The tunnel is being cleaned up closed The tunnel is being closed destroyed The tunnel is being destroyed established The tunnel is operating terminate The tunnel is terminating Unknown The tunnel is not connected to the router.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalIpAddrType.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalIpAddrType
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalIpAddrType.description: This object contains the type of the local end address of this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalIpAddress.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalIpAddress
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalIpAddress.description: This object contains the local end address of this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalUdpPort.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalUdpPort
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalUdpPort.description: This object contains the local end UDP port of this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalHostName.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalHostName
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsLocalHostName.description: This object contains the local host name of this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteHostName.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteHostName
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsRemoteHostName.description: This object contains the host name as discovered during the tunnel establishment phase (via the Host Name AVP) of the L2TP peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

jnxL2tpTunnelMaxSessions.name: jnxL2tpTunnelMaxSessions
jnxL2tpTunnelMaxSessions.description: This object represents the maximum number of sessions configured on this tunnel. It could be any positive number or unlimited (0).

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsWindowSize.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsWindowSize
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsWindowSize.description: This object contains the send window size for this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsHelloInterval.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsHelloInterval
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsHelloInterval.description: This object contains the hello interval for this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsCreationTime.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsCreationTime
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsCreationTime.description: This object represents the time of creation of this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsUpTime.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsUpTime
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsUpTime.description: This object represents the time elapsed since this tunnel was established.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsIdleTime.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsIdleTime
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsIdleTime.description: This object represents the time elapsed since this tunnel had last data activity (transmission or reception).

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsCollectionStart.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsCollectionStart
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsCollectionStart.description: This object represents the time at which the statistics gathering started for this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlTxPkts.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlTxPkts
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlTxPkts.description: This object contains the number of control packets that were transmitted to the tunnel peer.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlTxBytes.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlTxBytes
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlTxBytes.description: This object contains the number of control bytes that were transmitted to the tunnel peer.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlRxPkts.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlRxPkts
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlRxPkts.description: This object contains the number of control packets received on the tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlRxBytes.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlRxBytes
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsControlRxBytes.description: This object contains the number of control bytes that were received from the tunnel peer.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataTxPkts.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataTxPkts
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataTxPkts.description: This object contains the number of data packets transmitted to the tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataTxBytes.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataTxBytes
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataTxBytes.description: This object contains the number of data bytes that were transmitted to the tunnel peer.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataRxPkts.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataRxPkts
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataRxPkts.description: This object contains the number of data packets received from this tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataRxBytes.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataRxBytes
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsDataRxBytes.description: This object contains the number of data bytes that were received from the tunnel peer.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsErrorTxPkts.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsErrorTxPkts
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsErrorTxPkts.description: This object contains the number of error transmit packets on the tunnel.

jnxL2tpTunnelStatsErrorRxPkts.name: jnxL2tpTunnelStatsErrorRxPkts
jnxL2tpTunnelStatsErrorRxPkts.description: This object contains the number of error receive packets on the tunnel.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsTable.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsTable
jnxL2tpSessionStatsTable.description: The L2TP session status and statistics table. This table contains the objects that can be used to describe the current status and statistics of a single L2TP tunneled session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsEntry.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsEntry
jnxL2tpSessionStatsEntry.description: An L2TP session interface stats entry.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalTID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalTID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalTID.description: This object contains the local tunnel Identifier.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalSID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalSID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalSID.description: This object contains the local session Identifier.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsServiceInterface.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsServiceInterface
jnxL2tpSessionStatsServiceInterface.description: This object contains the name of the service interface on which this session is being hosted.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsTunnelGroup.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsTunnelGroup
jnxL2tpSessionStatsTunnelGroup.description: This object contains the name of the tunnel group that this session is part of.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteSID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteSID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteSID.description: This object contains the remote end assigned session identifier for this session. When a session is starting this value may be zero until the remote tunnel endpoint has responded.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsInterfaceUnit.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsInterfaceUnit
jnxL2tpSessionStatsInterfaceUnit.description: This object contains the interface unit number corresponding to the logical service interface on which the session is being hosted.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsEncapType.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsEncapType
jnxL2tpSessionStatsEncapType.description: This object contains the tunnel encapsulation type.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsBundleID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsBundleID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsBundleID.description: This object identifies the bundle that this session is a link of. This field is valid only for tunnel encapsulation type multilink-ppp.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsState.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsState
jnxL2tpSessionStatsState.description: This field contains the current state of the session - one of the internal session related state names as described below: established The session is operating closed The session is being closed destroyed The session is being destroyed cleanup The session is being cleaned up lns_ic_accept_new A new session is being accepted lns_ic_idle The session has been created and is idle lns_ic_reject_new The new session is being rejected lns_ic_wait_connect The session is waiting for the peer's incoming call connected (ICCN) message.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsUserName.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsUserName
jnxL2tpSessionStatsUserName.description: This object identifies the peer session name on this interface. This is typically the login name of the remote user. If the user name is unknown to the local tunnel peer then this object will contain a null string.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsMode.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsMode
jnxL2tpSessionStatsMode.description: This object identifies the configured mode value for this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalAddrType.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalAddrType
jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalAddrType.description: This object contains the type of the local end address of the tunnel that is hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalAddress.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalAddress
jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalAddress.description: This object contains the local end address of the tunnel that is hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalUdpPort.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalUdpPort
jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalUdpPort.description: This object contains the UDP port of the local end of the tunnel that is hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteAddrType.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteAddrType
jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteAddrType.description: This object contains the type of the remote end address of the tunnel hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteAddress.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteAddress
jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteAddress.description: This object contains the remote end address of the tunnel hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteUdpPort.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteUdpPort
jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteUdpPort.description: This object contains the UDP port of the remote end of the tunnel hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalHostName.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalHostName
jnxL2tpSessionStatsLocalHostName.description: This object contains the local host name of the tunnel that is hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteHostName.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteHostName
jnxL2tpSessionStatsRemoteHostName.description: This object contains the host name as discovered during the tunnel establishment phase (via the Host Name AVP) of the L2TP peer.

jnxL2tpSessionAssignedIpAddrType.name: jnxL2tpSessionAssignedIpAddrType
jnxL2tpSessionAssignedIpAddrType.description: This object contains the type of IP address of PPP client being tunneled as obtained from IPCP configuration during session establishment.

jnxL2tpSessionAssignedIpAddress.name: jnxL2tpSessionAssignedIpAddress
jnxL2tpSessionAssignedIpAddress.description: This object contains the IP address of the PPP client being tunneled as obtained from IPCP configuration during session establishment.

jnxL2tpSessionLocalMRU.name: jnxL2tpSessionLocalMRU
jnxL2tpSessionLocalMRU.description: The current value of the MRU for the local PPP Entity. This value is the MRU that the remote entity is using when sending packets to this session.

jnxL2tpSessionRemoteMRU.name: jnxL2tpSessionRemoteMRU
jnxL2tpSessionRemoteMRU.description: The current value of the MRU for the remote PPP Entity. This value is the MRU that the local entity is using when sending packets to the remote PPP client.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsTxSpeed.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsTxSpeed
jnxL2tpSessionStatsTxSpeed.description: This object returns the last known transmit baud rate for this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsRxSpeed.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsRxSpeed
jnxL2tpSessionStatsRxSpeed.description: This object returns the last known receive baud rate for this session established.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsCallBearerType.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsCallBearerType
jnxL2tpSessionStatsCallBearerType.description: This object describes the bearer type of this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramingType.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramingType
jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramingType.description: This object describes the framing type of this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsLCPRenegotiation.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsLCPRenegotiation
jnxL2tpSessionStatsLCPRenegotiation.description: This object returns whether LCP renegotiation is on or off for this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAuthMethod.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAuthMethod
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAuthMethod.description: This object contains the proxy authentication method employed by the LAC for the session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsNasIpAddrType.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsNasIpAddrType
jnxL2tpSessionStatsNasIpAddrType.description: This object contains the type of IP address of the RADIUS network address server to which the accounting records for this session are being sent to.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsNasIpAddress.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsNasIpAddress
jnxL2tpSessionStatsNasIpAddress.description: This object contains the IP address of the RADIUS network address server to which the accounting records for this session are being sent to.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsNasIpPort.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsNasIpPort
jnxL2tpSessionStatsNasIpPort.description: This object contains the port on which RADIUS network address server accounting messages will be sent.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramedProtocol.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramedProtocol
jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramedProtocol.description: This object contains the frame protocol attribute obtained from RADIUS server for this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramedIpAddrType.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramedIpAddrType
jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramedIpAddrType.description: This Attribute indicates the type of address to be configured for the user, as provided by the RADIUS server in response to authentication request.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramedIpAddress.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramedIpAddress
jnxL2tpSessionStatsFramedIpAddress.description: This Attribute indicates the address to be configured for the user, as provided by the RADIUS server in response to authentication request.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsCallingStationID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsCallingStationID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsCallingStationID.description: This Attribute allows the RADIUS NAS to send in the Access-Request packet the phone number that the call came from, using Automatic Number Identification (ANI) or similar technology. It is only used in Access-Request packets.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsCalledStationID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsCalledStationID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsCalledStationID.description: This Attribute allows the RADIUS NAS to send in the Access-Request packet the phone number that the user called, using Dialed Number Identification (DNIS) or similar technology. It is only used in Access-Request packets.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctDelayTime.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctDelayTime
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctDelayTime.description: This attribute indicates how many seconds the RADIUS accounting client has been trying to send a record for, and can be subtracted from the time of arrival on the server to find the approximate time of the event generating this Accounting-Request.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctSessionID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctSessionID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctSessionID.description: This attribute is a unique Accounting ID to make it easy to match start and stop records in a log file.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctMethod.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctMethod
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctMethod.description: This object contains the accounting method employed for this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctSessionTime.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctSessionTime
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctSessionTime.description: This attribute indicates how many seconds the user has received service for.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctNasPortType.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctNasPortType
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctNasPortType.description: This Attribute indicates the type of the physical port of the NAS which is performing accounting for the user.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlClientEndPoint.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlClientEndPoint
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlClientEndPoint.description: This object contains the remote tunnel Identifier of the tunnel hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlServerEndPoint.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlServerEndPoint
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlServerEndPoint.description: This object contains the local tunnel Identifier of the tunnel hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlClientAuthID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlClientAuthID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlClientAuthID.description: This object contains the host name as discovered during the tunnel establishment phase (via the Host Name AVP) of the L2TP peer, for the tunnel that is hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlServerAuthID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlServerAuthID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsAcctTnlServerAuthID.description: This object contains the local host name of the tunnel that is hosting this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsUserProfileName.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsUserProfileName
jnxL2tpSessionStatsUserProfileName.description: This object contains the configured access profile name that is being used for this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsInterfaceID.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsInterfaceID
jnxL2tpSessionStatsInterfaceID.description: This object contains the interface identification (name) for the session bearing service interface.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsCallSerialNumber.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsCallSerialNumber
jnxL2tpSessionStatsCallSerialNumber.description: This object contains the serial number that has been assigned to this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsCreationTime.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsCreationTime
jnxL2tpSessionStatsCreationTime.description: This object represents the time of creation of this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsUpTime.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsUpTime
jnxL2tpSessionStatsUpTime.description: This object represents the time elapsed since this session was established.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsIdleTime.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsIdleTime
jnxL2tpSessionStatsIdleTime.description: This object represents the time elapsed since this session had last data activity (transmission or reception).

jnxL2tpSessionStatsCollectionStart.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsCollectionStart
jnxL2tpSessionStatsCollectionStart.description: This object represents the time at which the statistics gathering started for this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlTxPkts.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlTxPkts
jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlTxPkts.description: This object contains the number of control packets that were transmitted to the session peer.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlTxBytes.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlTxBytes
jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlTxBytes.description: This object contains the number of control bytes that were transmitted to the session peer.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlRxPkts.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlRxPkts
jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlRxPkts.description: This object contains the number of control packets received on the session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlRxBytes.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlRxBytes
jnxL2tpSessionStatsControlRxBytes.description: This object contains the number of control bytes that were received from the session peer.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataTxPkts.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataTxPkts
jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataTxPkts.description: This object contains the number of data packets transmitted to the remote session peer.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataTxBytes.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataTxBytes
jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataTxBytes.description: This object contains the number of data bytes that were transmitted to the session peer.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataRxPkts.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataRxPkts
jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataRxPkts.description: This object contains the number of data packets received on this session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataRxBytes.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataRxBytes
jnxL2tpSessionStatsDataRxBytes.description: This object contains the number of data bytes that were received from the session peer.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsErrorTxPkts.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsErrorTxPkts
jnxL2tpSessionStatsErrorTxPkts.description: This object contains the number of error transmit packets on the session.

jnxL2tpSessionStatsErrorRxPkts.name: jnxL2tpSessionStatsErrorRxPkts
jnxL2tpSessionStatsErrorRxPkts.description: This object contains the number of error receive packets on the session.

jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsTable.name: jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsTable
jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsTable.description: The L2TP MLPPP bundle status and statistics table. This table contains the objects that can be used to describe the current status and statistics of a single L2TP tunneled multilink PPP bundle.

jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsEntry.name: jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsEntry
jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsEntry.description: An L2TP MLPPP bundle statistics entry.

jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsBundleID.name: jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsBundleID
jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsBundleID.description: This object identifies the session's associated bundle.

jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsNumLinks.name: jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsNumLinks
jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsNumLinks.description: This object identifies the current number of links that have joined the bundle.

jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsEndpoint.name: jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsEndpoint
jnxL2tpMlpppBundleStatsEndpoint.description: This object identifies the username of the MLPPP bundle.
